title: Band Iguana Hat to play Halloween party at Eagles
text: Band Iguana Hat to play Halloween party at Eagles Iguana Hat soaks up some sun. Print this article Advertisement The Walla Walla Blues Society has teamed up with the Walla Walla Eagles to sponsor a Halloween party, open to the public (age 21 and over), to start at 8 p.m. on Halloween evening, Oct. 31. The party will be at the Walla Walla Eagles Aerie, 350 S. Second Ave., next to the Stardust Lanes bowling alley. Live music will begin at 8:30 p.m., provided by the reunited regional favorite rockinâ€™ band Iguana Hat. The organizers say costumes are strongly encouraged. Cash prizes for costumes will be awarded in more than one category, and free door prizes will abound. Adult beverages will be available at the Eagles cash bar. Admission is $5.
